 # Java Client-Server Application

✅ Updated: Added Multi-Client Support and JSON Communication
This project demonstrates a client-server communication system using Java sockets with multi-client support.

## Technologies
- Java
- Socket / ServerSocket
- BufferedReader / PrintWriter
- JSON (for structured data communication)
- Multithreading (Thread-per-client)

## Features
- Server sends a mission (Auftrag)
- Client receives and displays it
- Client sends back a verification code
- Server verifies the code
- ✅ Supports:
  - Text-based communication
  - JSON-based communication
- ✅ Handles multiple clients simultaneously (Multi-Client Support)
- ✅ Each client is processed in a separate thread

## Description
The project was initially developed using simple text communication between a single client and the server.  

It was later improved by adding:
- JSON-based communication to structure the data
- Multi-client support using threads, allowing the server to handle multiple connections at the same time

This makes the system more flexible and closer to real-world networking applications.

## How to run
1. Start `Server.java`
2. Start one or more instances of `Client.java`
3. Each client will receive the mission
4. Enter the verification code (e.g. 007 or 008)

